    ObjectReaderWriter
    Class to read and write to serializable classes This allows us to save the state of an object and reload it when we run the program again This feature is used in our App to prevent hardcoding of "static" things like items in the menu which would have to be entered every time we run the program otherwise functions were written for all list classes but not all of them were used in the actual restaurant class due to the different natures of each object

    Order class which keeps track of all attributes for a "seating"
